Package: reportmagic
Type: Package
Title: Tools for Narrative-Friendly Reporting
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person(
      given = "Inma",
      family = "Ruiz",
      email = "roseneath12@outlook.com",
      role = c("aut", "cre")
    )
  )
Description: Tools for generating clear, human-readable narrative reporting from
    tabular data. The package provides small helper functions that make it easy
    to extract numeric values, format them consistently, and describe them in
    natural language. 
    - 'find_figure()' retrieves a single numeric value from a data frame based on
      a specified condition, ensuring clean and predictable extraction for use in
      reports.
    - 'magic_word()' compares an actual value with a rounded value and returns a
      narrative cue such as "over" or "almost" to support natural phrasing in
      analytical text.
    - 'pretty_number()' formats numbers for publication by applying rounding,
      fixed decimal places, and removing scientific notation.
    Together, these helpers support reproducible, expressive reporting workflows.
